    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-11-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-20T22:32:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Directs the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon the request of the licensee for project numbered 7307, to extend until December 31, 2007, the time required for commencement of project construction.</p> <p>Provides for reinstatement of an expired license.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>01</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-07-31</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to Senate with amendment(s)</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-20T22:32:14Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Directs the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon the request of the licensee for project numbered 7307, to extend until December 31, 2007, the time required for commencement of project construction.</p> <p>Instructs FERC to reinstate, effective as of the date of its termination, any license terminated before the enactment of this Act.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>35</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-11-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed Senate amended</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-20T22:32:28Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>(This measure has not been amended since it was reported to the Senate on July 31, 2006. The summary of that version is repeated here.)</b></p> <p>Directs the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon the request of the licensee for project numbered 7307, to extend until December 31, 2007, the time required for commencement of project construction.</p> <p>Instructs FERC to reinstate, effective as of the date of its termination, any license terminated before the enactment of this Act.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
